# Example file

This page lives inside a nested folder (`Tests/Getting Started/A folder inside a folder/`) and is here to prove that deeply nested subfolders show up correctly in the sidebar.

#s

## Media %{media}%

Audio, images and videos can use either a local file from your `assets/` folder or a remote URL.

!!!(assets/audio.mp3)

![A sample photo](assets/foto.png)

!!(assets/video.mp4)

## Links and headings %{links}%

External links open in a new tab by default:
[Example](https://example.com)

In-page headings work like a URL, but with a `#id` instead of the address:
[H2 in this page](#links)

A link to another page in your documentation uses the page path (remember to use `.html`, not `.mmx`):
[Introduction](pages/Introduction MMX.html)

